Duties &amp; Responsibilities

  Work with a team to develop software program/code as well as to generate robust test cases for rigorous code testing
  Exposed to the various stages of the SW Development Life Cycle from requirements analysis to software release.
  Participate in software integration activities leading to the successful acceptance testing of the completed product, system or solution
  Ability to troubleshoot and identify the root cause of issues under the interest of time
  Ability to perform under multi-task, dynamic environment with changing priorities
  Ability to effectively articulate technical challenges and solutions.

Qualifications/Requirements

  Degree in either Computer Science /Engineering/ Financial Accounting or any related fields
  Involved in Internship in any of ERP projects in modules such as Finance, Logistic or programming/code will be added advantage
  Strong fundamentals in object-oriented design, problem solving, and complexity analysis.
  Strong analytical and problem-solving skills
  Strong logical thinking ability
  Good communication skills, both verbal and written, in English
  Demonstrated skill and passion for operational excellence.
  Experience in any programming language
